data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Defining Quantum Computing**\n\nOkay, I'm working on a concise explanation of quantum computing, aiming for clarity. I've begun framing it as a novel computational approach. I'm focusing on defining the technology, and I'm outlining key elements, aiming to avoid over-technical detail, especially when describing the benefits of quantum computing.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"totalTokenCount": 75,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 67,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Refining Quantum Description**\n\nI'm now honing my explanation of quantum computing, focusing on clarity for a non-technical audience. I've rephrased \"process information differently\" to \"perform calculations in fundamentally new ways,\" to be more precise. The phrasing \"explore many possibilities at once\" is being strengthened by linking it directly to the power of qubits, and the advantages over existing classical computing.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"totalTokenCount": 320,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 312,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Clarifying Qubit Function**\n\nI'm now revising my explanation, focusing on the core concept of qubits and their operation. I want to convey how superposition lets qubits hold much more information than classical bits. I'm carefully choosing words to clarify the power of the superposition without getting bogged down in complex physics. I'm focusing on making a clear and digestible distinction for the audience.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"totalTokenCount": 565,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 557,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Crafting the Summary**\n\nI've just finished iterating on the quantum computing explanation, aiming for clarity and conciseness. I've rephrased for better flow and impact, settling on a version that balances core concepts with a focus on real-world applications and the unique capability of qubits. I've focused on direct, easy-to-understand language. I've also incorporated the user's focus on the problem types that are intractable on classical computers. I'm now pretty happy with the description.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"totalTokenCount": 809,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 801,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "**Finalizing the Explanation**\n\nI've just refined the explanation of quantum computing, aiming for both precision and accessibility. I've rephrased for better flow and impact, settling on a version that balances core concepts with a focus on real-world applications and the unique capability of qubits. I'm satisfied with the phrasing and conciseness, especially the emphasis on intractability for classical computers. I believe the explanation effectively communicates the essence of quantum computing to the target audience.\n\n\n","thought": true}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"totalTokenCount": 835,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 827,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": "Quantum computing is a new type of computing that leverages principles of quantum mechanics, such as superposition and entanglement, to"}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"candidatesTokenCount": 17,"totalTokenCount": 852,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 827,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": " perform calculations in fundamentally different ways than classical computers. Instead of bits that are either 0 or 1, quantum computers use \"qubits\" which can exist as 0, 1, or both simultaneously (superposition), and can"}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"candidatesTokenCount": 65,"totalTokenCount": 900,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 827,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

data: {"candidates": [{"content": {"parts": [{"text": " be quantumly linked (entanglement). This unique capability allows quantum computers to process vast amounts of information in parallel and solve certain complex problems—like simulating molecular interactions for drug discovery, designing new materials, optimizing logistics, or breaking modern encryption—"}],"role": "model"},"index": 0}],"usageMetadata": {"promptTokenCount": 8,"candidatesTokenCount": 113,"totalTokenCount": 948,"promptTokensDetails": [{"modality": "TEXT","tokenCount": 8}],"thoughtsTokenCount": 827,"serviceTier": "standard"},"modelVersion": "gemini-2.5-flash","responseId": "puz_aeX5Hbi3_uMP67rnwQU"}

